    public class ViewTransitionResult<T,K>
extends ChainedTransitionResult<T,K>
    A Form result generating a View Transition. This is essentially a ChainedTransitionResult with a null key but with the destination a "bookmarkable" location so in HTML it uses a redirect not a forward. The TransitionServlet will convert this to a plain ChainedTransitionResult before processing. In non web contexts the two representations are identical.

    • Method Detail

      • useURL

        public boolean useURL()
        Description copied from class: ChainedTransitionResult
        Is this a transition to a bookmarkable location. In web implementations if this method returns true then we redirect to the URL instead of just forwarding to logic. This means the page is at a URL that can be bookmarked. It is also useful for results from state changing operations as this prevents the back button from re-submitting the operation.
        Overrides:
        useURL in class ChainedTransitionResult<T,K>
        Returns:
        true if URL needed
